deo game developer [[Ascaron]] filed for bankruptcy in June 2009, Gaming Minds Studios GmbH was incorporated by the Kalypso Media Group, and added 15 former [[Ascaron]] employees to the studio\u2019s roster. Kalypso Media Group also acquired the rights to many of Ascaron's games, and also handed these development duties to Gaming Minds Studios.  In July 2010, Berlin manufacturer The Games Company filed for bankruptcy and in September, Kalypso Media Group took over, acquiring several brands owned by the insolvent company.  Following this, Kalypso Media Group also took on 17 employees of The Games Company and its studio [[Silver Style Entertainment]], moving operations to a newly founded Berlin outlet, [[Noumena Studios]] . In 2014, [[Noumena Studios]] was renamed Skilltree Studios and in 2016, it closed its doors.\n\nFrom March 2013 to August 2014, the Kalypso Media Group released its own intermittent podcast called the KalypsoCast.  From November 2013 and the podcast\u2019s eleventh edition, an accompanying video version was uploaded to Youtube. Regular guests on the KalypsoCast included former Kalypso Media Group CEO Stefan Marcinek, PR manager Bernd Berheide, and producers and product managers Christian Schl\u00fctter, Timo Thomas and Dennis Blumenthal. In April 2014, Kalypso Media Mobile GmbH was founded in [[Berlin]]. The studio\u2019s first mobile and tablet games were released a year later in May, 2015.\n\nIn January 2016, Stefan Marcinek sold his shares in the Kalypso Media Group and left the company, leaving Simon Hellwig as sole shareholder.\n\nSince July 2018, all rights to the titles of [[Pyro Studios]] ([[Commandos (series)|''Commandos'']], ''[[Imperial Glory]]'', [[Praetorians (video game)|''Praetorians'']]) have been added to the Kalypso Media Group\u2019s portfolio.\n\n== Subsidiaries ==\nKalypso maintains several of its own development studios:\n* Realmforge Studios was established in Munich in 2008 incorporating the team of Boxed Dreams who had developed ''[[Ceville]]''. Realmforge oversees development on the ''[[Dungeons (video game)|Dungeons]]'' series of games\n* Gaming Minds Studios was established in [[G\u00fctersloh]] in June 2009 following the bankruptcy of [[Ascaron]], incorporating fifteen Ascaron developers into the team. Gaming Minds develops games in the ''[[Railway Empire]]'' and ''[[Port Royale: Gold, Power and Pirates|Port Royale]]'' series.\n* Claymore Game Studios was established in [[Darmstadt]] in December 2019, and is working on a new game in the [[Commandos (series)|''Commandos'']] series.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.mcvuk.com/business-news/kalypso-media-opens-new-studio-in-frankfurt/ | title = Kalypso Media opens new studio in Frankfurt | first =Vikki | last = Blake | date = December 11, 2019 | accessdate = April 2, 2020 | work = [[MCVUK]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2020-04-02-third-internal-kalypso-studio-revealed-as-claymore-game-studios | title = Third internal Kalypso studio revealed as Claymore Game Studios | first = Matthew | last = Handrahan | date = April 2, 2020 | accessdate = April 2, 2020 | work = [[GamesIndustry.biz]] }}</ref>\n\n== Notable games published ==\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n! Release date \t\n! Title \t\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2020\n| [[Spacebase Startopia]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2020\n| [[Port Royale 4]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n|2020\n|Immortal Realms: Vampire Wars\n|\n|-\n| 2019\t\n| [[Tropico 6]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2018\t\n| [[Shadows: Awakening]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2018\t\n| [[Railway Empire]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2017\t\n| [[Dungeons 3]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2017\t\n| [[Vikings: Wolves of Midgard]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2017\t\n| [[Sudden Strike 4]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2017\t\n| [[Urban Empire]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2015\t\n| [[Crookz: The Big Heist]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2015 \t\n| [[Grand Ages: Medieval]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2015\t\n| [[Dungeons 2]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2014\t\n| [[Tropico 5]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2013\t\n| [[Dark (video game)|Dark]]\t\n|\t\n|-\n| 2013\