s3 = 9  | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2011\u20132013 | clubs4 = [[Doxa Drama F.C.|Doxa Drama]]          | caps4 = 40 | goals4 = 2\n| years5 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs5 = [[Niki Volou FC|Niki Volos]]            | caps5 = 26 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2014\u20132016 | clubs6 = [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]          | caps6 = 30 | goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs7 = [[AC Omonia|Omonia]]                    | caps7 = 20 | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2017\u20132018 | clubs8 = [[PAE Kerkyra|Kerkyra]]                 | caps8 = 11 | goals8 = 0\n| years9 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs9 = [[FC Boto\u0219ani|Boto\u0219ani]]                | caps9 = 24 | goals9 = 0\n| years10= 2019\u2013     | clubs10= [[FCSB]]                                | caps10= 14 | goals10= 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2010\u20132012 | nationalteam1 = [[Greece national under-21 football team|Greece U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 13 | nationalgoals1 = 1\n| club-update = 21:21, 22 February 2020 (UTC).\n| ntupdate = 31 December 2012\n}}\n\n'''Aristidis Soiledis''' ({{lang-gr|\u0391\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a3\u03bf\u03ca\u03bb\u03ad\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2}}; born 8 February 1991) is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Full back (association football)|left back]] for Romanian club [[FCSB]].\n\n==Club career==\nSoiledis started his career football career at [[Olympiakos F.C.|Olympiacos]]. He made his first team debut in Super League against [[Levadeiakos]] during the 2008\u20132009 season coming as a substitution for [[Sebastian Leto]]. Acknowledging his potential and in order to gain much needed experience, the team soon loaned him for two successive seasons to [[OFI Crete|OFI]] and [[Levadiakos]]. On 31 August 2011, [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiakos]] announced the release of the player, who did not succeed to gain sufficient time with the first team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/en/article/2699/soiledis-released-%E2%80%93-vasilogiannis-and-katai-loan-apollon-limassol-and-ofi-respectively|publisher=olympiacos.org|title=Soiledis released }}</ref>\nAfter his release from Olympiakos he signed a two-year contract with [[Doxa Drama]] playing in [[Football League]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novasports.gr/news.aspx?a_id=203433&Sport=1&Competition=1729&Season=87777&Country=82&Team=17265&Round=205617|publisher=novasports.gr|title=\"\u039c\u03b1\u03c5\u03c1\u03b1\u03b5\u03c4\u03cc\u03c2\" \u03bf \u03a3\u03bf\u03ca\u03bb\u03ad\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2}}</ref> On 1 August 2013 the 22-year-old midfielder signed a 1+1-year contract with \"blue white\" in [[Football League]] aiming the accession to [[Super League]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pamesports.gr/253312/kai-epishma-sth-nikh-voloy-o-soiledhs|publisher=pamesports.gr|date=1 August 2013|title=\u039a\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b5\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u039d\u03af\u03ba\u03b7 \u0392\u03cc\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5 \u03bf \u03a3\u03bf\u03ca\u03bb\u03ad\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2|access-date=1 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140605051215/http://www.pamesports.gr/253312/kai-epishma-sth-nikh-voloy-o-soiledhs|archive-date=5 June 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 June 2014, Soiledis signed a three-year deal with [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aekfc.gr/index.asp?a_id=1355&n_id=8565|title=Agreement with Aris Soiledis|language=Greek|accessdate=7 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714125105/http://www.aekfc.gr/index.asp?a_id=1355&n_id=8565|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 6 July 2016, he mutually solved his contract with [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdna.gr/podosfairo/superleague/article/219915/telos-kai-episima-o-soiledis-apo-tin-aek|title=\u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b5\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 \u03bf \u03a3\u03bf\u03ca\u03bb\u03ad\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u0395\u039a|language=Greek|accessdate=6 July 2016}}</ref> having 41 appearances (2 goals, 5 assists) in all competitions. On 7 July 2016, he signed a contract with Cypriot club [[AC Omonia|Omonia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/Cyprus/sthn-omonoia-o-soiledhs.4157117.html|title=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039f\u03bc\u03cc\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9\u03b1 \u03bf \u03a3\u03bf\u03ca\u03bb\u03ad\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2|language=Greek|accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref> On 15 July 2017 he returned to the [[Greek Superleague|Superleague]] joining [[PAE Kerkyra|Kerkyra]] on a one-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Kerkyra/ypegrapse-sthn-kerkyra-o-soiledhs.4767715.html |title=\u03a5\u03c0\u03ad\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c8\u03b5 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039a\u03ad\u03c1\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bf \u03a3\u03bf\u03ca\u03bb\u03ad\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2 |publisher=sport24.gr |date=15 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 July 2018, Soiledis signed a year contract with Romanian [[Liga I]] club [[FC Boto\u0219ani]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.libertatea.ro/sport/soiledis-aristeidis-semnat-cu-fc-botosani-2298763 |title=Soiledis Aristeidis a semnat cu FC Boto\u0219ani. Moldovenii s-au reunit |publisher=libertatea.ro |date=19 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHe appeared for the [[Greece national under-21 football team]] 13 times.\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n''Statistics accurate as of match played 22 February 2020.''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ro.soccerway.com/players/aristides-soiledis/76633/|title=A. Soiledis|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=12 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA#Club|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"3\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|[[2007\u201308 Superleague Greece|2007\u20130